One person died after a truck transporting recycling materials knocked down a wall in Johannesburg on Wednesday. Netcare911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said the incident happened about 9.25am on the corner of Kruger and Marshall streets in the Johannesburg CBD. Herbst said the tipper truck knocked down an 8m portion of a wall, which then collapsed on two people. One man was declared dead on the scene while a woman sustained moderate injuries to her lower limbs. She was transported to hospital.